h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new Confluence page
# Create a new Code Block Macro (whilst not required, enabling "show line numbers" makes the issue easier to see)
# Type the following code into the Code Box Macro
{code:title=Sample Text}
// comment

// comment

method A
{
}

method B
{
}
{code}
(!) Copy and Pasting the above works as intended, the bug only presents on keyboard inputs
# Save the page

h3. Expected Results
An output like
{code:JAVA|title=Expected Output}
// comment

// comment

method A
{
}

method B
{
}
{code}

h3. Actual Results
The following output
{code:JAVA|title=Actual Output}
// comment


// comment


method A
{
}


method B
{
}
{code}

Each new empty line added results in double empty lines in the output.

These empty lines are reflected in the editor when the page is edited.
 
h3. Notes
Copy and pasting bypasses this issue.

h3. Work Around
Create the code in a text editor and copy it into the text box.

Alternately, the code can be created Code Box Macro, copied into a text editor, and then copied back from the text editor into the Code Box Macro.

Simply copying the Code Box Macro content to clipboard and pasting it back into the macro will not suffice.
